  {±1}  U(1)  SU(2)  (Moufang loop)

**The Structural Endpoint:**
  𝕆 is non-associative (proved by witness: (e₁e₂)e₄ ≠ e₁(e₂e₄))
  But the embedded ℍ ⊂ 𝕆 IS associative
  The tower cannot extend: Hurwitz + Adams

**The Complete Pattern:**

    ℝ ════════╗
    ║  Knot I ║
    ℂ ════════╬═══════╗
    ║ Knot II ║       ║
    ℍ ════════╬═══════╬═══════╗
    ║ Knot IV ║       ║       ║
    𝕆 ════════╝  Knot III    Knot V
    ║                 ║       ║
    (TOWER ENDS)      ║       ║
    ║                 ║       ║
    ╚═════════════════╝═══════╝

    S⁰ ──→ S¹ ──→ S³ ──→ S⁷         (fibers)
    Δ₁ ←── Δ₂ ←── Δ₄ ←── Δ₈         (Laplacians)
    1      2      4      8  → 16?   (dimensions)
    ℝ      ℂ      ℍ      𝕆  → 𝕊?    (algebras)
                              ↑
                         zero divisors!
                         (Hurwitz, 1898)

    The tower is not infinite.  It is a FOUR-LEVEL structure,
    terminated by the failure of associativity at 𝕆 and the
    appearance of zero divisors at 𝕊.

    The four Hopf fibrations:
      S⁰ → S¹ → S¹     (real)
      S¹ → S³ → S²     (complex)
      S³ → S⁷ → S⁴     (quaternionic)
      S⁷ → S¹⁵ → S⁸    (octonionic)

    are ALL the Hopf fibrations of spheres (Adams, 1960).

                        ∎
-/

end HopfTowerKnot
